# Commit Discipline

When asked to commit work:

- Split unrelated changes into separate commits in implementation order.
- Use clear commit messages that describe the purpose of each change.
- Do not commit runtime caches, logs, credentials, session state, or other sensitive/generated files.
- Before committing, inspect staged changes and keep each commit focused.
